children.text: There are roof trusses that have been installed out of plumb, outside the maximum allowable tolerances documented in the standards.
The truss manufacturer’s erection tolerances, and the relevant Australian Standard, AS 4440 Installation of Nail-Plated Timber Roof Trusses, states that

‘Tolerance is critical for both a good roof line and effective bracing. Trusses to be erected so that no part of the truss is out of plumb with a tolerance exceeding the lesser of height/50 and 50 mm’ ;

These trusses must be properly plumbed back to within the Australian Standards and manufacturer’s allowable erection tolerances otherwise they may possibly fail. Alternatively, the builder should provide the owner with documentation from the manufacturer to confirm that the current installation is acceptable.
